# Audit artifacts are EXPLICITLY tracked — every security review belongs on GitHub.
# Prior versions of this file ignored `SECURITY_AUDIT_*.md`, `findings_*.txt`, and
# `/*.docx` which silently dropped post-rule audits from version control
# (caught SECURITY_AUDIT_300_AGENT.md, the canonical reference). Keep these files
# in tree. If a genuine scratch / working buffer needs to stay out, prefix with
# a leading dot (e.g. `.audit_findings.md`, `.spartan_unpacked/`) which is
# already covered by general dotfile conventions.
# Do NOT add SECURITY_AUDIT_*.md / findings_*.txt / tegridy_*.docx back to ignore.
